.TH "drm_framebuffer_remove" 9 "drm_framebuffer_remove" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_framebuffer_remove \- remove and unreference a framebuffer object
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_framebuffer_remove
.BI "(struct drm_framebuffer *fb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fb" 12
framebuffer to remove
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Scans all the CRTCs and planes in \fIdev\fP's mode_config.  If they're
using \fIfb\fP, removes it, setting it to NULL. Then drops the reference to the
passed-in framebuffer. Might take the modeset locks.

Note that this function optimizes the cleanup away if the caller holds the
last reference to the framebuffer. It is also guaranteed to not take the
modeset locks in this case.
